text:
152 Mill Lane, south side, between East 45th and East 46th Streets, known once as No. 6 Mill Lane and in 1928 as 1588 East 46th Street; it being situated a short distance west of East 46th Street and Mill Lane, having gone out of existence. This is the Joseph White house, built in 1816 and remodeled in 1855.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
